name: Decreased Follicle-Stimulating Hormone levels in blood
description: A reduction in the circulating concentration of follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH), a key regulator of follicular growth and maturation in the ovary.

name: Increased apoptosis of granulosa cells in ovary
description: An increase in the rate of programmed cell death in the somatic cells that surround the oocyte within an ovarian follicle, often resulting from the withdrawal of essential survival signals like FSH.

name: Increased follicular atresia in ovary
description: An increase in the degeneration and resorption of ovarian follicles before they reach maturity, leading to a reduction in the number of viable, growing follicles.

name: Disruption of menstrual cycle
description: Alterations in the normal rhythm and length of the menstrual cycle, often manifesting as infrequent or prolonged cycles (oligomenorrhea) due to impaired follicular development.

name: Reduced fertility
description: A diminished capacity to conceive or produce offspring, which may manifest as an increased time required to achieve pregnancy (subfertility).
